			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	TRUSTe has an opening for a multi-faceted operations engineer. We are looking for someone who can hit the ground running, loves getting his/her hands dirty, and has the ability to solve complex problems and situations. Great communication skills and ability to multitask are a must. In short, if you are looking for an opportunity to make a discernible&nbsp; and immediate difference in a growing company, TRUSTe is the place for you.<br />
	<br />
	Overview:<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Systems administration<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support of development, test and production environments<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Machine configuration and deployment<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitoring tools<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Code deployment to production<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Systems backup<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network configuration<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working with data center providers<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working with CDNs<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Contract administration<br />
	<br />
	Core Areas of responsibility:<br />
	<br />
	Applications and Architecture:<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in design, implementation and management/maintenance of customer and internal applications and architecture<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with engineering to develop and architect system infrastructure<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in the design of system infrastructure and architecture providing automation, scalability, reliability and performance that will grow as TRUSTe&rsquo;s business grows<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and maintain operations administrative procedures and enhance existing ones.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand all software components and architecture and how they work end-to-end<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide escalation support for system issues and incidents.<br />
	<br />
	Network:<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Set up and maintain load balancers, routers, switches and other networking equipment in the production data centers<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design network architecture topography for the production environment<br />
	<br />
	Operations:<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor production systems for performance and reliability<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Response to trouble events<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide systems troubleshooting as they pertain to network,<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; File problem reports<br />
	<br />
	Requirements:<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BS or MS degree in Computer Science or other technical discipline<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum of 3 to 5 years configuring and administering Linux, database and networking systems in a production environment<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The ability to take initiative, solve problems, and communicate effectively in a strong team focused environment<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to quickly learn new technologies with minimal ramp-up time<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with configuration management systems<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of Linux kernel configuration, performance monitoring, and tuning<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong background in internet service deployment, provisioning, IP networking, service infrastructure, and software deployment<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge deploying and maintaining database infrastructure<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of administrative scripting languages &ndash; Shell, Perl, Python, etc.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working with load balancing technologies and web server farms<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience troubleshooting; Ethernet based networks and TCP/IP based services, IP routing protocols, firewalls<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Required to participate in 24x7 on-call rotation with a mobile phone and remote connectivity<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to lift a minimum of 50lbs.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-starter and self-motivated with excellent analytical, planning, and communication, project tracking and management (both written and verbal)<br />
